# Commit Early, Commit Often

**Commit after each logical unit completes, not in batches at the end.**

## When to Commit

After completing:
- A new type definition or interface
- A parsing/discovery function + its tests
- A single MCP tool/resource registration
- A refactoring of one piece
- Documentation for one feature

## Constraint

**< 8 files, < 500 lines per commit.** Split larger changes.

## Why

- Errors caught immediately (small delta = easy debug)
- Each commit is a safe checkpoint
- User can give feedback after each commit
- Commit message documents intent

